     C
      ** +--- Start of Main processing -----------------------------------+
      ** ¦                                                                ¦
      ** ¦ Initial processing is performed automatically: the *INZSR is   ¦
      ** ¦ executed at program activation.                                ¦
      ** ¦                                                                ¦
      ** +----------------------------------------------------------------+
 
      ** Initialization
 
     C                   MOVE      *BLANK        RetCodeIn
 
     C                   MOVE      *BLANK        FldNamXAr
     C                   MOVE      *BLANK        MsgIDXAr
     C                   MOVE      *BLANK        MsgDtaXAr
     C                   Z-ADD     0             Idx
 
      ** comments
 
      *
      ** VALIDATION
      *
     C                   EXSR      CIDAV
      *
      ** If an error was found, set the return code appropriately
      *
     C     DDCIDAOK      IFEQ      'N'
     C                   EVAL      RetCodeIn = 'Error'
     C                   ENDIF
      *
      * RETURN
      *
     C                   RETURN
      *****************************************************************
     C/EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      ** VALIDATION - Validate CHIPS ID
      *****************************************************************
     C     CIDAV         BEGSR
 
      * If CHIPS ID is entered
     C     DDCIDA        IFEQ      *BLANK
     C                   Z-ADD     *ZEROS        CUCHID
 
     C                   ELSE
 
     C                   MOVE      *BLANKS       WKCIDA
     C                   MOVE      DDCIDA        WKCIDA
 
      * must be numeric
     C                   CALL      'ZALIGN'
      ** Return Code (7A)
      ** CHIPS ID alpha (16A)
      ** Number of Decimals (1,0)
      ** Number of Digits (2,0)
      ** CHIPS ID numeric (16A)
     C                   PARM                    @RTCD             7
     C                   PARM                    WKCIDA           16
     C                   PARM      *ZERO         DECIMALS          1 0
     C                   PARM      6             DIGITS            2 0
     C                   PARM      *BLANK        WKCHID           16
      *
     C     @RTCD         IFNE      *BLANK
     C                   MOVE      'N'           DDCIDAOK
     C                   ADD       1             Idx
     C                   MOVEL     'DDCIDA'      FldNamXAr(Idx)
     C                   MOVEL     'USR0822'     MsgIdXAr(Idx)
 
     C                   ELSE
 
     C                   MOVE      WKCHID        CUCHID
     C                   MOVE      WKCHID        DDCIDA
     C                   END
     C                   END
     C                   ENDSR
      *****************************************************************
      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      * *INZSR - Program Initialisation routine                       *
      *****************************************************************
     C     *INZSR        BEGSR
 
     C     *ENTRY        PLIST
      *
      * INPUTS
      *
      ** Return Code
     C                   PARM                    RetCodeIn
      *
      ** CHIPS ID alpha (6A)
     C                   PARM                    DDCIDA            6
      *
      * OUTPUTS
      *
      * Error fields/message IDs/message data (arrays) from/to caller
     C                   PARM                    FldNamXAr
     C                   PARM                    MsgIDXAr
     C                   PARM                    MsgDtaXAr
      *
      ** CHIPS ID - OK
     C                   PARM                    DDCIDAOK          1
      *
      ** CHIPS ID numeric (6,0)
     C                   PARM                    CUCHID            6 0
      *
      ** Program, module and procedure names for database error processing.
      ** =================================================================
      ** The following /COPY sets these values, and also defines LDA as
      ** an external data area
 
     C/COPY ZACPYSRC,DBFIELDS
 
     C                   ENDSR
